Create the index.handlebars file inside views directory.

Create the layouts directory inside views directory.

Create the main.handlebars file inside layouts directory.

Setup the main.handlebars file so it's able to be used by Handlebars.

Setup the index.handlebars to have the template that Handlebars can render onto.

Create a button in index.handlebars that will submit the user input into the database. --}}

<h1>Burgers!</h1>

<h2>Burger List!</h2>

<div class ="main row">
  <ul>
    {{#each burgers}}{{#unless devoured}}
      <li>
        <p class = "burgerType">{{this.burger_name}}</p>
        <form action ="api/burgers/{{this.id}}?_method=PUT" method="POST" class="dev">
          <input type ="hidden" name ="devoured" value ="true">
          <button class="btn" type ="submit">Devour burger</button>
        </form>      
      </li>
    {{/unless}}
  {{/each}}
</ul>
</div>

<h2>Devoured!</h2>

  <ul>
    {{#each burgers}}{{#if devoured}}
      <li>
        <p class="burgerType">{{this.burger_name}}</p>
      </li>
    {{/if}}
  {{/each}}
</ul>

<h2>Add a Burger</h2>

<form class = "form-inline" action = "api/burgers/" method = "POST">
  <div class = "form-group">
    <input type = "text" class = "form-control" name = "name" placeholder="Enter burger">
  </div>
  <button type = "submit" class ="btn">Submit Hamburge</button>
</form>
